"But the muscle is the machinery affected and set into motion, and the nerves are the delicate telegraphic wires leading to the parts.",0,0,0,0,0,0
And so it is with this transmission of the mental waves and currents.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The brain of the Transmitter, aroused by his active _Will_, sends a powerful current or wave through his nervous system.",1,1,0,1,1,0
"When it reaches the extremity of his fingers it leaps over the tiny space separating his nerves from the nerves of the Receiver, and enters the nervous system of the latter, and influences his actions.",1,1,0,1,1,0
"The Receiver being in a passive condition, and his brain sending practically no impulses over his nerves, he is in a receptive condition to the imparted nervous current, which acts upon him something like an impulse from his own brain, only weaker.",1,1,1,1,1,1
