A WORD OF WARNING.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Beginning your entertainment, caution the audience about placing the hidden objects in places that you cannot conveniently touch--such as high up on the wall; under the strings of a piano, etc.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Tell them that you can _find_ the article anywhere, but it must be placed so that you can get at it with only ordinary care and work.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"Some Smart Alicks may try to play pranks on you in this way, but discourage same vigorously at the start, informing the audience that this is a scientific test and not a circus.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"And, remember this, tell them that the article must never be hidden about the Transmitter, for the reason that he is seldom able to think as intently about his own location as about some place away from him.",1,1,0,1,1,0
